# Spend approval — never spend without an estimate and my OK

Applies to EVERY chat in EVERY folder. Before triggering ANY action that costs
money on a paid API (OpenAI text/image generation, etc.):

1. ESTIMATE first. State the expected USD cost (per item and total) before running anything.
2. WAIT for my explicit approval. Do not make the paid call until I say yes.
3. Only then run it WITH the explicit confirmation the tool requires.

## Shared budget — all folders share ONE daily cap
- Policy: `~/.seo-pipeline/budget.json` (`daily_usd_cap`, `require_approval`).
- Live daily tally: `~/.seo-pipeline/.spend_ledger.json` (one shared file, keyed by date).
- Default cap is **$1.00/day across ALL folders combined**. Never raise it without asking me.

## How to actually spend (only after I approve)
- Image script (e.g. Sauna): `node scripts/gen-images.mjs ... --yes`. Omit `--yes`
  or add `--dry` to get an estimate with no charge.
- Content API CLI: add `--yes`. HTTP API: add `"confirm": true`. Without these you
  get an estimate-only response and nothing is charged.
- Prefer the cheapest option that works: `--quality low`, `n=1`, fewer items.

## Hard rules
- Never bypass these guardrails. Never hardcode `confirm:true` / `--yes` into scripts or defaults.
- If a tool has no estimate/approval mechanism, STOP and tell me before spending.
- Default image quality for tests is "low" unless I explicitly ask for higher.
